From 82e3a496eb56da0b9f29fdc5b63cedb3289e91de Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Corentin Labbe <clabbe@baylibre.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Dec 2021 17:16:26 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] media: staging: media: zoran: move videodev alloc
Git-commit: 82e3a496eb56da0b9f29fdc5b63cedb3289e91de
Patch-mainline: v5.18-rc1
References: CVE-2021-47644 bsc#1237766

[ backport note: due to the large code difference between the upstream
  code (at that time) and the target branch code, here we concentrate
  only on the memory leak fix, and cover it just by calling kfree() at
  zoran_remove() instead of the full backport -- tiwai ]

Move some code out of zr36057_init() and create new functions for handling
zr->video_dev. This permit to ease code reading and fix a zr->video_dev
memory leak.

Signed-off-by: Corentin Labbe <clabbe@baylibre.com>
Signed-off-by: Hans Verkuil <hverkuil-cisco@xs4all.nl>
Signed-off-by: Mauro Carvalho Chehab <mchehab@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/media/pci/zoran/zoran_card.c |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/drivers/media/pci/zoran/zoran_card.c
+++ b/drivers/media/pci/zoran/zoran_card.c
@@ -1112,6 +1112,7 @@ static void zoran_remove(struct pci_dev
 	iounmap(zr->zr36057_mem);
 	pci_disable_device(zr->pci_dev);
 	video_unregister_device(zr->video_dev);
+	kfree(zr->video_dev);
 exit_free:
 	v4l2_ctrl_handler_free(&zr->hdl);
 	v4l2_device_unregister(&zr->v4l2_dev);
